The paper proposes a statistical framework for detecting and imputing localized data corruptions, which involves algorithms for separating anomalies and imputing corrupted data. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and statistics (cs.ST). The paper uses machine learning datasets to test the proposed framework, which further supports the relevance of the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories.
